column25: ,key=[7.1.1.1/H-0-1]: [id="2_2_1_hardware" data-text=" 2.2.1. Hardware "> 2.2.1. Hardware Handheld device implementations:

,key=[7.1.1.1/H-1-1]: [ MUST have at least one Android-compatible display that meets all requirements described on this document. [7.1.1.3/H-SR] Are STRONGLY RECOMMENDED to provide users an affordance to change the display size (screen density). If Handheld device implementations support software screen rotation, they:

,key=[7.1.1.1/H-2-1]: [* MUST make the logical screen that is made available for third party applications be at least 2 inches on the short edge(s) and 2.7 inches on the long edge(s). Devices which launched on an API level earlier than that of this document are exempted from this requirement. If Handheld device implementations do not support software screen rotation, they:

,key=[7.1.4.5/H-1-1]: [* MUST make the logical screen that is made available for third party applications be at least 2.7 inches on the short edge(s). Devices which launched on an API level earlier than that of this document are exempted from this requirement. If Handheld device implementations claim support for high dynamic range displays through Configuration.isScreenHdr() , they:

,key=[7.1.4.6/H-0-1]: [ MUST advertise support for the EGL_EXT_gl_colorspace_bt2020_pq, EGL_EXT_surface_SMPTE2086_metadata, EGL_EXT_surface_CTA861_3_metadata, VK_EXT_swapchain_colorspace, and VK_EXT_hdr_metadata extensions. Handheld device implementations:

,key=[7.1.4.6/H-1-1]: [ MUST report whether the device supports the GPU profiling capability via a system property graphics.gpu.profiler.support. If Handheld device implementations declare support via a system property graphics.gpu.profiler.support, they:
,key=[7.1.4.6/H-1-2]: [ MUST report as output a protobuf trace that complies with the schema for GPU counters and GPU renderstages defined in the Perfetto documentation.
,key=[7.1.4.6/H-1-3]: [ MUST report conformant values for the device’s GPU counters following the gpu counter trace packet proto.
,key=[7.1.4.6/H-1-4]: [ MUST report conformant values for the device’s GPU RenderStages following the render stage trace packet proto.

,key=[7.5.4/H-1-1]: [ MUST provide the data saver mode. If Handheld device implementations include a logical camera device that lists capabilities using CameraMetadata.REQUEST_AVAILABLE_CAPABILITIES_LOGICAL_MULTI_CAMERA, they:

,key=[3.8.16/H-1-1]: [ MUST declare the support of managed profiles via the android.software.managed_users feature flag, except when the device is configured so that it would report itself as a low RAM device or so that it allocates internal (non-removable) storage as shared storage. If Handheld device implementations include support for ControlsProviderService and Control APIs and allow third-party applications to publish device controls, then they:
,key=[3.8.16/H-1-2]: [ MUST declare the feature flag android.software.controls and set it to true.

,key=[3.8.16/H-1-3]: [ MUST provide a user affordance with the ability to add, edit, select, and operate the user’s favorite device controls from the controls registered by the third-party applications through the ControlsProviderService and the Control APIs.
,key=[3.8.16/H-1-4]: [ MUST provide access to this user affordance within three interactions from a default Launcher.

,key=[3.8.16/H-2-1]: [ MUST accurately render in this user affordance the name and icon of each third-party app that provides controls via the ControlsProviderService API as well as any specified fields provided by the Control APIs. Conversely, If Handheld device implementations do not implement such controls, they:
,key=[3.8.16/H-2-2]: [ MUST report null for the ControlsProviderService and the Control APIs.

,key=[3/A-1-1]: [ MUST support all public APIs in the android.car.* namespace. If Automotive device implementations provide a proprietary API using android.car.CarPropertyManager with android.car.VehiclePropertyIds, they:
,key=[3/A-1-2]: [ MUST NOT attach special privileges to system application's use of these properties, or prevent third-party applications from using these properties.
,key=[3.2.3.1/A-0-1]: [ MUST support and enforce all permissions constants as documented by the Automotive Permission reference page.
